randoop
Class PrimValue

Object
  PrimValue
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, ObjectContract
public final class PrimValue
extends Object
implements ObjectContract

An observation recording the value of a primitive value obtained during execution, (e.g. var3 == 1 where var3 is an integer-valued variable in a Randoop test).

Obviously, this is not a property that must hold of all objects in a test. Randoop creates an instance of this contract when, during execution of a sequence, it determines that the above property holds. The property thus represents a regression as it captures the behavior of the code when it is executed.

evaluate

public boolean evaluate(Object... objects)
                 throws Throwable
Description copied from interface: ObjectContract
Evaluates the contract on the given values.

When calling this method during execution of a test, Randoop guarantees that objects does not contain any null objects, and that objects.length == getArity().

This method should return true if the contract was satisfied and false if it was violated.

toCodeString

public String toCodeString()
Description copied from interface: ObjectContract
A string that can be used as Java source code and will result in the expression being evaluated.

The string should be formatted as follows: the N-th object that participates in the expression should be referred to as "xN" (for N one of 0, ... , 9). For example, if the expression or arity 2 represents a call of the equals method between two objects, the comment should be something like "x0.equals(x1)".

The returned string should not be null.

Specified by:
toCodeString in interface ObjectContract

evalExceptionMeansFailure

public boolean evalExceptionMeansFailure()
Description copied from interface: ObjectContract
Communicates to Randoop how to interpret exceptional behavior from the evaluate method.

If this method returns true, Randoop will interpret an exception that escapes during evaluation as a failure of the contract.

If the method returns false, Randoop will interpret an exception as passing behavior.

Specified by:
evalExceptionMeansFailure in interface ObjectContract
